Alnus japonica

   [3023.jpg]
    Authority   (Thunb.) St.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Hamamelidae:Fagales:Betulaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names Japanese alder, aune du Japon, amieiro do Japao
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3023

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A small to medium-sized tree reaching a height of
   2-10 m. Often with a crooked trunk, closely spaced branches and a dense
   crown. USES It can be grown as an ornamental, for enrichments planting
   beneath pines, and as a shade tree. Mentioned as a possible
   agroforestry species. GROWING PERIOD Perennial. The tree may withstand
   a dry season of 4-6 months. COMMON NAMES Japanese alder. FURTHER INF
   Japanese alder is native of northeastern Asia and Taiwan. It occurs
   naturally at elevations between 1000-1500 m, but grows well down to 600
   m.

   Sources
   SOURCES (Alnus japonica (Thunb.) Steud.)
   Hensleigh T 1988 pp 23-30 [USE, LIG, TEXT, DRA, FER, PH, TEMP, RAIN]

